
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="description" content="Web-Push demo application">
    <meta name="author" content="Florent Morselli, from Spomky-Labs">
    <title>Web Push Demo</title>

    <link rel="canonical" href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.1/examples/starter-template/">

    <title>{% block title %}Web Push Demo!{% endblock %}</title>
    {% block stylesheets %}
        {{ encore_entry_link_tags('app') }}
    {% endblock %}
</head>
<body>

<div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto p-3 py-md-5">
    <header class="d-flex align-items-center pb-3 mb-5 border-bottom">
        <a href="/" class="d-flex align-items-center text-dark text-decoration-none">
            <span class="fs-4">Web Push Demo üì®</span>
        </a>
    </header>
    <main>
        <h1>Get started with Web Push Notifications</h1>
        <p class="fs-5 col-md-8">Quickly and easily get started with Web Push Notification using the Spomky-Labs‚Äô library or Symfony bundle</p>
        <div class="mb-5">
            <a href="https://github.com/Spomky-Labs/web-push" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-4">View the source code</a>
        </div>

        <hr class="col-3 col-md-2 mb-5">

        <div class="row g-5">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h2>Before</h2>
                <p>
                    Web Push Notifications shall be explicitly allowed by the end user.
                    Please click on the dedicated button below to enable that feature.
                    <br>
                    It can can disabled at any time!
                </p>
                <button class="btn btn-info btn-lg px-4" id="push-subscription-button">Push notifications !</button>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h2>After</h2>
                <p>
                    When enabled, the server will be able to receive the associated subscription dataset
                    and send you notifications.
                    <br>
                    For this demo, <em>nothing is stored on the server side</em>. The button below simulates a fully featured notification
                    you will show on your device.
                    <br>
                    <strong>Just hit the button to give it a try!</strong>
                </p>
                <button class="btn btn-success btn-lg px-4" id="send-push-button">Send a push notification</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
    <footer class="pt-5 my-5 text-muted border-top">
        Made with ‚ù§Ô∏è by Spomky-Labs &middot; &copy; 2021
    </footer>
</div>
{% block javascripts %}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('app') }}
{% endblock %}
</body>
</html>
